ing-information","subChapters":[{"id":"e43fc276-0f45-52d9-97a9-394af935add3","slug":"topical-ear-preparations","fullItemName":"Topical ear preparations"},{"id":"b49a03f2-59c1-56ed-b894-9e01ce84d1a8","slug":"oral-analgesics","fullItemName":"Oral analgesics"},{"id":"fd97664d-7f15-5f36-a10c-7bcad2d057f2","slug":"oral-flucloxacillin","fullItemName":"Oral flucloxacillin"},{"id":"b186879f-d6d6-5afa-84d8-845ba42605c1","slug":"oral-clarithromycin","fullItemName":"Oral clarithromycin"}]},{"id":"8c363337-fc91-521b-a609-58b9b0ba4d8b","fullItemName":"Supporting evidence","slug":"supporting-evidence","subChapters":[]},{"id":"9feebcb7-db7f-5a9f-a9a7-89f401ebca13","fullItemName":"How this topic was developed","slug":"how-this-topic-was-developed","subChapters":[{"id":"8fc4ebd8-033e-5184-bb1e-cc1bd7de86e2","slug":"search-strategy","fullItemName":"Search strategy"},{"id":"7580e3ff-a6f6-5f7b-9254-6772074d8d7b","slug":"stakeholder-engagement","fullItemName":"Stakeholder engagement"},{"id":"5162da22-b23f-5934-87a8-4aa96029fcde","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria"},{"id":"babd7947-def4-5d00-a46e-c68902688a88","slug":"organizational-behavioural-financial-barriers","fullItemName":"Organizational, behavioural and financial barriers"},{"id":"18fd5166-b294-56f8-8cf1-c2e4e2bfa31d","slug":"declarations-of-interest","fullItemName":"Declarations of interest"}]},{"id":"ae1ef912-929f-5085-9b08-d75ce3e016b7","fullItemName":"References","slug":"references","subChapters":[]}]},"parentChapter":{"id":"1851ae55-865c-5488-902c-54822a2a76dd","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Management"},"subChapters":[{"id":"b3c45d3a-783d-5887-a770-449b78e272a0","slug":"management","fullItemName":"Management","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 5b1a9b80-1e90-4482-8d04-052ea0ec2905 --><h3>How should I manage someone with localized otitis externa?</h3><!-- end field 5b1a9b80-1e90-4482-8d04-052ea0ec2905 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 3088c923-83f8-41a4-ac39-5e9e330b81b2 --><!-- begin field d2c6f8d1-44be-4bc7-b7c6-7e43b655171d --><ul><li><strong>Treat the pain if present:</strong><ul><li>Treat with an analgesic and the application of local heat (for example a warm flannel). These measures are sufficient for most cases of localized otitis externa as folliculitis is usually mild and self-limiting.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Treat infection if necessary:</strong><ul><li>Oral antibiotics are rarely indicated. Only consider an oral antibiotic for people with severe infection, or at high risk for severe infection, for example if:<ul><li>Furunculosis or cellulitis spreads beyond the ear canal to the pinna, neck, or face.</li><li>There are systemic signs of infection, such as fever.</li><li>The person has a medical condition which is associated with increased risk of severe infection (such as diabetes mellitus, or compromised immunity).</li></ul></li><li>If an oral antibiotic is required, consider are a 7-day course of flucloxacillin<em>, </em>or clarithromycin (if the person is allergic to penicillin).</li></ul></li><li><strong>Drain pus if necessary:</strong><ul><li>If pus is causing severe pain and swelling, consider incision and drainage.<ul><li>This is rarely required.</li><li>Incision and drainage usually requires referral, although a small pustule near the entrance to the ear canal may be drained by incising it with a surgical needle.</li></ul></li></ul></li><li><strong>Provide appropriate <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/otitis-externa/management/localized-otitis-externa/#self-care-advice\">self-care advice</a> to aid recovery and to reduce the risk of future infection.</strong></li></ul><!-- end field d2c6f8d1-44be-4bc7-b7c6-7e43b655171d --><!-- end item 3088c923-83f8-41a4-ac39-5e9e330b81b2 -->","subChapters":[{"id":"e2c847b8-c9ff-5d16-a5b1-d9c0f9f6ba43","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-5d7","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":4,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 720345f6-2ed2-45b4-81d5-6455d38113fd --><h4>Basis for recommendation</h4><!-- end field 720345f6-2ed2-45b4-81d5-6455d38113fd -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 5d72122e-031d-4cfa-a183-5ff483b75eb1 --><!-- begin field 2def6cf3-3275-4dba-8648-69c9531cbd73 --><p>CKS found no evidence or guidelines specifically on furunculosis in the external ear canal. These recommendations are pragmatic, based on the most likely causative organism (<em>Staphylococcus aureus</em>) and expert opinion from the medical literature on how furunculosis should be treated [<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/otitis-externa/references/\">Laube, 2004</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/otitis-externa/references/\">Sladden and Johnston, 2005</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/otitis-externa/references/\">McNulty, Personal Communication, 2006</a>].</p><!-- end field 2def6cf3-3275-4dba-8648-69c9531cbd73 --><!-- end item 5d72122e-031d-4cfa-a183-5ff483b75eb1 -->","subChapters":[]}]},{"id":"2ca965e6-3bc7-58fe-acfb-d407fe1a453d","slug":"self-care-advice","fullItemName":"Self-care advice","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field c756b182-e40b-49e8-b0b6-097818cd52c7 --><h3>Self-care advice</h3><!-- end field c756b182-e40b-49e8-b0b6-097818cd52c7 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 06187c32-9e06-4882-9d57-bac6ee6e8707 --><!-- begin field 07a1356a-2a7f-401f-8bed-0924fc3bdb53 --><ul><li><p>For information on self-care, see the section on <a class=\"topic-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/otitis-externa/management/acute-diffuse-otitis-externa/#self-care-advice\">Self-care advice.</a></p></li></ul><!-- end field 07a1356a-2a7f-401f-8bed-0924fc3bdb53 --><!-- end item 06187c32-9e06-4882-9d57-bac6ee6e8707 -->","subChapters":[]},{"id":"e648c623-62f9-5700-ab86-7d10bf487781","slug":"follow-up","fullItemName":"Follow up","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field c9bbe567-dcde-4933-98d4-b60111c2e727 --><h3>What follow up is required for people with localized otitis externa?</h3><!-- end field c9bbe567-dcde-4933-98d4-b60111c2e727 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 0e5e4f91-ca0e-40a8-a775-1efc1fe5ed79 --><!-- begin field 0d9f1b9a-26be-4e67-9ed9-e036975562c6 --><ul><li>Follow up is not normally necessary for acute localized otitis externa, as it is usually mild and self-limiting. However, consider follow up if: <ul><li>An oral antibiotic has been prescribed.</li><li>The person has underlying medical conditions, such as diabetes mellitus, or if they are immunocompromised. </li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 0d9f1b9a-26be-4e67-9ed9-e036975562c6 --><!-- end item 0e5e4f91-ca0e-40a8-a775-1efc1fe5ed79 -->","subChapters":[{"id":"60eb1b26-745b-5a7a-9ef8-088ca10ae271","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-a97","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":4,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 21e3283f-33f7-4c4d-81b1-25e557adb1b3 --><h4>Basis for recommendation</h4><!-- end field 21e3283f-33f7-4c4d-81b1-25e557adb1b3 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item a97cdfc3-b26b-4588-91c4-1db6fd299adb --><!-- begin field d99deb61-0bc4-4784-9ed2-d6b1f8369333 --><p>CKS found no evidence or guidelines on managing localized otitis externa. These recommendations are pragmatic and what CKS considers good clinical practice.</p><!-- end field d99deb61-0bc4-4784-9ed2-d6b1f8369333 --><!-- end item a97cdfc3-b26b-4588-91c4-1db6fd299adb -->","subChapters":[]}]},{"id":"c379fef8-504f-5180-8a1a-e72339639c1a","slug":"when-to-refer-or-seek-medical-advice","fullItemName":"When to refer or seek medical advice","depth":3,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 334019ad-00ff-468f-8d90-270aa3e64aad --><h3>When should I refer, or seek specialist advice, for someone with localized otitis externa?</h3><!-- end field 334019ad-00ff-468f-8d90-270aa3e64aad -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 7bb9712e-3e6a-4dda-8812-a20ac0102524 --><!-- begin field 99c63cfd-cd2d-455c-aac1-d08e39a14bc1 --><ul><li>Consider referral to secondary care:<ul><li>If relief of pain and swelling requires incision and drainage of the furuncle, and the resources and skills are not available in primary care.</li><li>If there is inadequate response to oral antibiotic treatment.</li><li>If cellulitis is spreading outside the auditory canal.</li></ul></li></ul><!-- end field 99c63cfd-cd2d-455c-aac1-d08e39a14bc1 --><!-- end item 7bb9712e-3e6a-4dda-8812-a20ac0102524 -->","subChapters":[{"id":"4956d57e-6eac-5af8-8160-f068666dae21","slug":"basis-for-recommendation-5f9","fullItemName":"Basis for recommendation","depth":4,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 4ce1cc0c-71ed-4fc5-9b16-b5b3baa8c5d6 --><h4>Basis for recommendation</h4><!-- end field 4ce1cc0c-71ed-4fc5-9b16-b5b3baa8c5d6 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 5f9e5ed1-a514-4a97-b2b3-c3c5e7ea4f29 --><!-- begin field 00e0054a-e441-49b8-ae44-9908d8599e8d --><p>These recommendations are pragmatic advice as CKS was unable to find relevant evidence or guidelines.</p><!-- end field 00e0054a-e441-49b8-ae44-9908d8599e8d --><!-- end item 5f9e5ed1-a514-4a97-b2b3-c3c5e7ea4f29 -->","subChapters":[]}]}]}}},"staticQueryHashes":["3666801979"]}